We can be called New York pizza snobs and have had a hard time finding a good pie here in Cape Coral until we tried Sicily Trattoria's pizza--It was not only the best pizza we have had here but I  can say that it just might be the best pizza we have ever had! It is absolutely delicious , fresh perfectly done dough with a light brown crust--perfect texture, a very good sauce a little more sweet then salty and very good cheese that wasn't greasy--it was so good we couldn't believe it...thanks for knowing how to do pizza right!
A fantastic pizza with great service, highly recommended!

This restaurant has always been our favorite for spaghetti and meatballs. My friend and I would always make a point of dining here at least once during our stay in Cape Coral. However, on our last visit we were a bit disappointed in some of the changes to our service. They now do an up charge of 3$ if you want to share your meal:( whereas before this was never an issue, they even split the food on the plate before serving it to us. Also, the ceasar salad that accompanied the meal was so sparse that you could literally see the bottom of the plate. I have never seen a salad so small ( I wish I would have taken a photo). Also, it appears that the portion size of the spaghetti and meatballs has been downsized as well. We can no longer share a meal there and we will be forced to order each our own. We were very surprised and still hungry when we left. We literraly went to another restaurant afterwards to eat.

This review is for pizza only. To be fair, I have not tried their lunches or dinners. I will review them another time. Now...I come from the NJ/Philly area. One of the greatest pizza markets in the country. What I had tonight didn't really compare to what I'm used to getting in a pizza. In my humble opinion the crust was too thin and had a burnt flour taste to it. Almost tasted like cracker. The sauce (which should be the flavor base of the pie) was very bland and lacked any trace of spices. The cheese had a great flavor and even melt accross the pie. It was actually the highlight of the pie. As I said in the beginning, I will try their dinners at a later date. Until then.. Eat out often and demand good food. You are paying for it!

We visit beautiful Cape Coral every year and this is our favorite restaurant that keeps getting better and better.  This is our first time back since their remodel and it is beautiful.  Happy to say that the food is still 5 Stars!  Their minestrone is divine and this time I had their Alla Vodka with the homemade pasta.  It is so wonderful.  My husband had Spaghetti  with olive oil and extra garlic.  Beyond words.  The best part of our visit here is the family that runs it.  They are an extremely great group of people that make you feel like family.  I wish we could take y'all home with us.  Thank you.
Newly decorated, great food and reasonably priced table wine.  My only request is they should have olive oil available for the bread.
What a great family owned restaurant.  They never disappoint and everyone leaves with a full belly and a smile!

This restaurant is a hidden gem in Cape Coral.  The service was excellent and the sauces were amazing on their pasta.  It's a relaxed atmosphere.  We did not try their pizza, but they looked spectacular, both deep dish and traditional.  Only 4 stars for the fact they were out of their soup and homemade pasta.  Thankfully, everything was so good I will have to go back to try them!

Vinny (the owner) just took care of my families party celebrating the life of my mom after the funeral. The food and service was great and all 26 people were stuffed. Great true Italian restaurant. Thanks Vinny

Tonight my girlfriend and I went to Sicily Trattoria in the cape for dinner. I think they are still working out the kinks from the expansion , and we're pretty crowded so getting our food took a bit. But the waitress was always attentive to our table and very apologetic for the delay.  As for the food, we split a pizza and it was very tasty, and well priced in my opinion. We will definitely be coming back in the future.

I went there the other night with my wife and daughter for some dinner. So my wife just asked if she could use the restroom and was told "Absolutely not, Its for paying customers only" Well had they not turned us away, We would have been paying customers. With so many other pizza joints in the cape, You would think they would at least try to be polite maybe just a little bit. So sorry, We will not be back nor will we recommend you to anyone.
